                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d126">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">818.51/1100: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Des Portes</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="59" xml:id="d126fn59">The Legation in Costa Rica was
                        elevated to the status of Embassy on May 20, 1943, when Ambassador Fay Allen
                        Des Portes, succeeding Minister Robert M. Scotten, presented his credentials
                        to the Costa Rican Government.</note>
                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-15T19:00:00-06:00"
                            >July 15, 1943—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:59 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>537. Reference my telegram No. 536, July 15, 11 a.m.,<note n="58"
                        xml:id="d126fn58">Not printed.</note> and Department’s airgram No. 396,
                    April 3. The President has just informed me that the Supreme Court decision was
                    favorable to the fruit company by a vote of 4 to 1 and that the decision will be
                    made public early next week.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Des Portes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
